{% # Exploration: subgrid bleed grid v1.0.0 %}

{% comment %}
  Stage 0 verification scaffold for the subgrid migration. Demonstrates the new named-line bleed grid model on `<theme-section>` with six representative cases. Each case is a direct child of theme-section (or two siblings: a label + the demonstration block); section's `grid-column` rules in `assets/layer-theme.css` resolve positioning.

  Reachable at /?view=exploration--subgrid. Temporary scaffold per BACKLOG.md § Active exploration.
{% endcomment %}

<theme-section data-modifiers="theme-root,color-scheme:scheme-1">
  <header class='subgrid-intro'>
    <h1>Subgrid bleed grid — Stage 0 verification</h1>
    <p>
      Six cases exercising the new named-line bleed grid on <code>&lt;theme-section&gt;</code>. Each demonstration block sits as a direct child of the section; its <code>bleed-desktop</code> / <code>bleed-mobile</code> modifiers gate <code>grid-column</code> rules on the section's named bleed lines (<code>bleed-start</code> / <code>content-start</code> / <code>content-end</code> / <code>bleed-end</code>). See <code>.context/docs/subgrid-migration.md</code>.
    </p>
  </header>

  {% comment %} ---- Case 1: section-bleed band ---- {% endcomment %}
  <header class='case-label'>
    <h2>1. Section-bleed band</h2>
    <p>Full-bleed strip (desktop + mobile); content-track sibling below.</p>
  </header>
  <div class='demo demo--bleed' data-modifiers='bleed-desktop:both,bleed-mobile:both'>
    bleed-desktop:both · bleed-mobile:both → grid-column: bleed-start / bleed-end
  </div>
  <div class='demo demo--content'>
    Sibling below (no bleed) → grid-column: content-start / content-end (default)
  </div>

  {% comment %} ---- Case 2: hero image-left + content-right ---- {% endcomment %}
  <header class='case-label'>
    <h2>2. Hero, image-left bleed</h2>
    <p>Asymmetric: media bleeds to the start edge, content stays in track.</p>
  </header>
  <div class='demo demo--hero' data-modifiers='bleed-desktop:inline-start'>
    <div class='demo__media'>media (bleeds inline-start)</div>
    <div class='demo__copy'>
      <h3>Hero copy</h3>
      <p>Sits inside the demonstration block's own grid. Block as a whole spans bleed-start → content-end.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  {% comment %} ---- Case 3: hero image-right + content-left (mirrored) ---- {% endcomment %}
  <header class='case-label'>
    <h2>3. Hero, image-right bleed</h2>
    <p>Mirrored asymmetric: media bleeds to the end edge.</p>
  </header>
  <div class='demo demo--hero demo--hero-mirror' data-modifiers='bleed-desktop:inline-end'>
    <div class='demo__copy'>
      <h3>Hero copy</h3>
      <p>Content on the start side; media on the end side bleeds to viewport edge.</p>
    </div>
    <div class='demo__media'>media (bleeds inline-end)</div>
  </div>

  {% comment %} ---- Case 4: two-track columns, both bleeding ---- {% endcomment %}
  <header class='case-label'>
    <h2>4. Two-track band, both bleeding</h2>
    <p>Full-bleed band with two equal-width content tracks inside.</p>
  </header>
  <div class='demo demo--two-track' data-modifiers='bleed-desktop:both,bleed-mobile:both'>
    <div class='demo__track'>track 1 — sits inside block's own grid</div>
    <div class='demo__track'>track 2 — sits inside block's own grid</div>
  </div>

  {% comment %} ---- Case 5: three-track columns, content-aligned ---- {% endcomment %}
  <header class='case-label'>
    <h2>5. Three-track columns, content-aligned</h2>
    <p>No bleed: block stays in content track; tracks split content-width.</p>
  </header>
  <div class='demo demo--three-track'>
    <div class='demo__track'>track 1</div>
    <div class='demo__track'>track 2</div>
    <div class='demo__track'>track 3</div>
  </div>

  {% comment %} ---- Case 6: nested groups inside section-bleed columns ---- {% endcomment %}
  <header class='case-label'>
    <h2>6. Nested groups inside section-bleed columns</h2>
    <p>Outer columns bleeds full width; inner groups sit inside columns' own tracks. Inner groups carry bleed modifiers, but section's <code>&gt;</code> selector only matches direct children — nested bleed silently no-ops, demonstrating the strict container-only model.</p>
  </header>
  <div class='demo demo--two-track' data-modifiers='bleed-desktop:both'>
    <div class='demo__track demo__nested-group' data-modifiers='bleed-desktop:both'>
      <small>nested with bleed-desktop:both — does NOT bleed (positions in outer track)</small>
    </div>
    <div class='demo__track demo__nested-group'>
      <small>nested without bleed — positions in outer track</small>
    </div>
  </div>
</theme-section>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Subgrid exploration",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "shopify-section--exploration--subgrid",
  "settings": []
}
